-------^xFFFF77Crafting Guide^7-------- Note: this crafting is only for the higher end gear. life+resist gear you can just craft with greed essence, harvest reforge life or just buy from trade as it's usually cheap. Note when eldritch crafting your implcitis you want your desired mod to be lower tier then your undesired mod before orb of conflicting, this slightly increased the chance of succeeding. This only works until exceptional tier.
^xFFFF77Quiver^7: Buy a fractured +1 arrow or T1 multi base, preferable on feathered arrow quiver. Needs to be at least ilvl 81, (ilvl 86 is ideal though) 1) Spam contempt essence until you hit T1 multi (or +1 arrow if you have a fractured multi base). 2) You now need 2 empty prefixes and 1 empty suffix. Annul if you need to, high chance to brick and if it does, back to step 1. 3) Craft cannot roll attack and use a combination of exalts/annuls until your desired life/increased damage with bow skills. When you have "craft cannot roll attack" you wont be able to annul your +1 arrow, or multi or flat physical damage. And your only exalt outcomes are maximum life and increased damage with bows skills.
^xFFFF77Body armour:^7 Buy a T1 resist fractured evasion chest or spell suppression (but resist is probably a lot cheaper). 1) Spam any resist essence until you hit T1 or T2 spell suppression. 2) Use wild bristle matreon in bestiary for a cheap "suffixes cannot be changed" and then use harvest reforge life, repeat until t1 or t2 life.
^xFFFF77Helmet:^7^7 Buy a T1 chaos resist fractured. 1) Spam spite essence until T1 or T2 spell suppression. 2) Use wild bristle matreon in bestiary for a cheap "suffixes cannot be changed" and then use harvest reforge life, repeat until t1 or t2 life.
^xFFFF77Gloves With abyss socket. ^7To start off you need to buy gloves with either "increased damage against chilled enemies" or "added fire damage against burning enemies" or "increased critical strike chance vs shocked enemies" The base type of these do not matter as you will recomb. 1) Recomb these gloves with velour gloves. The best method I found is just to scour your velour gloves, recomb and pray. 2) After you have the modifier on your gloves, feel free to use the harvest res swap bench to get your ideal temple mod/cheaper method then divining. Then use a fracturing orb and hope it hits 3) Now use the fossil combo of hollow-shuddering-sanctified until t1 attack speed. Can also annul for an open suffix, then lock suffixes and reforge speed (if you remove the abyss socket, then go back to fossils). 4) Use wild bristle matreon in bestiary for a cheap "suffixes cannot be changed" and then harvest reforge life until t1 or t2 life.
^xFFFF77Basic gloves (cheaper).^7 Buy a T1 chaos resist fractured. 1) Spam zeal essence until any t1 res (then use harvest res swap for whatever resistance you're missing). 2) Use wild bristle matreon in bestiary for a cheap "suffixes cannot be changed" and then use harvest reforge life, repeat until t1 or t2 life.
^xFFFF77Boots:^7 Buy a T1 resist fractured evasion chest or spell suppression (but resist is probably a lot cheaper). 1) Spam any resist essence until you hit T1 or T2 spell suppression. 2) Use wild bristle matreon in bestiary for a cheap "suffixes cannot be changed" and then use harvest reforge life, repeat until t1 or t2 life. ^7 ^xFFFF77Medium Clusters:^7 1) You just spam harvest reforge speed, annul/exalt when needed. Can also fracture a t1 mod if you want to make a 4xT1 medium cluster. (have 3 mods, so the fracture has a 75% chance of succeeding).
^xFFFF77Large Clusters 12 passive: ^7 1) Fracture 35% effect, can go for 3% attack speed/35% effect for a 50/50 fracture. 2) Spam harvest reforge speed and exalt/annul when you hit 3/4 mods. Spam reforge life if you have 3% attack speed fractured. This is a long and costly process. Can settle for t2 life, but you need 3% attack speed/35% effect/4% all res.
